ont></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelvay.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elvay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/02 9:12:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10253.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Off-hand damage questions..</span><hr size=1> I am coming from a hardcore caster background so weapons in my hands is a bit new to me.. I have a quick question about offhand damage.. I read somewhere that your offhand doesn't get a damage bonus? This confuses me becuase I use a LSoEE in my off hand and often see 50's to 60's on the 16 dam weapon.. <br><br>Could someone explain offhand damage to me?<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unotwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>notwen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/02 9:28:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10253.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Off-hand damage questions..</span><hr size=1> Damage is calculated the same as for main hand, you just don't getthe strength bonus.  The part that might be confusing you on the LSOEE is the MAGIC damage bonus on the blade, that makes the base damage more like 21. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uevertorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evertorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/02 9:41:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10253.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Off-hand damage questions..</span><hr size=1> Actually, you mean damage bonus notwen.<br><br>As notwen stated both weapons are calculated the same, the only difference is that your main hand recieves a damage bonus (you'll see an area on the weapon description that says Dmg bonus: X where X is the bonus for your level). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubeldukil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beldukil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/02 11:51:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10253.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Off-hand damage questions..</span><hr size=1> at 60, 1h damage bonus is 11 extra damage per hit.  You do not get this on the off hand <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvalrog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valrog</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/02 12:10:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10253.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Off-hand damage questions..</span><hr size=1> Which means your minimum hit in your primary is 1 + Dmg Bonus For Your Level and in the offhand it is simply 1 - Because the Dmg Bonus that is displayed on your Weapons doesnt work on your off-hand as was said above. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showPrevMessage?topicID=10253.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showNextMessage?topicID=10253.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10253.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.emailToFriend?topicID=10253.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.threadControl?topicID=10253.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10253.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10253.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies